From: art-suite conda packaging
Subject: [PATCH] Add missing <algorithm>/<cassert>/<cstdint>/<limits> includes

Same implicit-standard-header reliance as art (#8) / fhiclcpp (#4): several
art_root_io TUs use std::find_if, assert(), fixed-width ints or std::numeric_limits
without including the owning header. Older libstdc++ leaked them transitively;
conda's newer libstdc++ does not. Add the direct includes (IWYU), non-test TUs
only (BUILD_TESTING=OFF). Each file gets exactly the headers it needs, inserted
after its first #include. See conda/potential_improvements.md (#9).

